1. Under the compliance portal go to communication compliance
2. Policy tab
3. Create new policy > custom policy
4. Enter a name for your custom policy
5. Enter a description for you custom policy
6. Choose the users and groups within your organization who this policy will apply to
7. Specify the group members to be excluded from the policy
8. Choose users to review the communications that are returned by this policy.
9. Choose locations to detect communications
10. Choose conditions and review percentage
  - Add Condition
  - Content contains any of these sensitive info types
  - Add sensitive info types
  - Select the sensitive info type you created using the How to create custom word dictionaries guide
  - Add options like OCR and review percentages
11. Finish and create policy
  
